<TITLE> Ship breaking yard explosion kills two </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Dec 26 (bdnews24.com)  Two people were killed and 10 others injured after a gas cylinder exploded at a scrap ship in Sitakunda breaking yard on Saturday, police said. Sitakunda police chief Monirul Islam said the explosion occurred while workers were engaged in dismantling a scrap ship at Rahim Steel and Ship Breaking Yard at around 10:30am. One body has been identified as Selim Hossain. Some of the injured were admitted to Sitakunda upazila health complex and a few severely injured workers were taken to Chittagong Medical College Hospital, Islam said. Ships are being broken into pieces for use in re-rolling mills without any precautionary measure that often causes accidents. bd
